Seems a lot has been going on in the past few months, and a few things came to a head recently. I always find that friends are one of my most valuable resources and I try my hardest to keep them, and keep them happy. I'm a people pleaser plain and simple, but I'm starting to realize that it's not worth it. If you spend all of your time tyring to please everyone then you yourself will never be happy, you yourself will never get anywhere, and when you reach that point in your life where you begin to reflect on what you've accomplished your going to be highly disappointed. I'm not saying fuck-it in regards to friends and such, but really is it worth stressing over if so and so likes me or if so and so really is my friend. It's funny how when you are infactuated with someone you see no fault, they are the best person in the world and nothing can change your mind, but when you slowly start to see clearly you find many faults, you see that person for what they really are. Life is funny like that it loves you pull the wool over your eyes, and just as your content with being blind it rips it off and you are exposed to the harsh harsh light. Coming to realize that some people aren't what you make em for, and that's just how life is. Am I really who I think I am? I think I'm a nice, considerate, caring person, but does that come across to other people???? I don't know......I don't know at all and that's what scares me to a certain degree. I am also fearful of failure and just not knowing what I want...it all seemed cut and dry, but now it's hazy and confusing. Hmph Life loves to deal you fucked up hands, so what do you do? Do you roll with the punches, do you just buckle and succumb or do you smack it around like a cheap floozy on a Saturday night? Who knows...certainly I don't, but when I find the answer I'll be sure to share!
